description: Non-Material Amendment to Planning Permission 2013/02259/RES granted 22 August 2013, amendment sought to merge residential plots 878 and 879 into one residential unit, merge plots 900, 904 and 963 into one residential unit and merge plots 896 and 897 into one residential unit in Blocks F and provide four additional Two-Bedroom units in Block G.  Submission of reserved matters relating to external appearance and landscaping for Buildings F and G, pursuant to hybrid planning permission ref: 2012/04253/VAR granted 26th February 2013, comprising a mixed use development of 489 residential units, 1,190 sq.m of commercial floorspace (Use Class A1-A5), 8,896 sq.m of office floorspace (Use Class B1), within seven buildings (B to H) ranging from six to eight storey's in height, and a 25 storey tower (Building A); formation of water basin, two canals and navigable lock to replace existing Chelsea Creek barrier gates; provision of public and private open space; cycle and 402 car parking spaces at basement level.
